<div class="zm-item-rich-text" data-resourceid="2895098" data-action="/answer/content">

<div class=" zm-editable-content clearfix"><p>把网格玩到极致，就变成了，玄♂学。</p><br><noscript><img src="//pic3.zhimg.com/4f1da09f16abafdb465bf6201e2891ae_b.jpg" data-rawheight="620" data-rawwidth="1077" class="origin_image zh-lightbox-thumb" width="1077" data-original="//pic3.zhimg.com/4f1da09f16abafdb465bf6201e2891ae_r.jpg"></noscript><img src="//s1.zhimg.com/misc/whitedot.jpg" data-rawheight="620" data-rawwidth="1077" class="origin_image zh-lightbox-thumb lazy" width="1077" data-original="//pic3.zhimg.com/4f1da09f16abafdb465bf6201e2891ae_r.jpg" data-actualsrc="//pic3.zhimg.com/4f1da09f16abafdb465bf6201e2891ae_b.jpg"><br><p>当然，不是真·玄♂学。<br></p><p>这种网格现在常见于大气物理计算，用来瓜分地球：</p><noscript><img src="//pic3.zhimg.com/46bdff2404701addf807292e0ea39ee6_b.jpg" data-rawheight="389" data-rawwidth="832" class="origin_image zh-lightbox-thumb" width="832" data-original="//pic3.zhimg.com/46bdff2404701addf807292e0ea39ee6_r.jpg"></noscript><img src="//s1.zhimg.com/misc/whitedot.jpg" data-rawheight="389" data-rawwidth="832" class="origin_image zh-lightbox-thumb lazy" width="832" data-original="//pic3.zhimg.com/46bdff2404701addf807292e0ea39ee6_r.jpg" data-actualsrc="//pic3.zhimg.com/46bdff2404701addf807292e0ea39ee6_b.jpg"><br><p>原始出处参考文献：</p><p><a href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/wol1/doi/10.1029/2004GC000734/full" class=" wrap external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer">“Yin-Yang grid”: An overset grid in spherical geometry<i class="icon-external"></i></a></p><p>作者叫Akira Kageyama（秋本影山？一股二次元的感觉。）</p><br><p>感兴趣的可以看一看作者的主页：</p><p><a href="http://www.research.kobe-u.ac.jp/csi-viz/members/kageyama/yin_yang_grid/index.html" class=" wrap external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Kageyama / Portal to Yin-Yang Grid<i class="icon-external"></i></a></p><br><p>内有很多相关链接，还有Mathematica源码：</p><p><a href="http://www.research.kobe-u.ac.jp/csi-viz/members/kageyama/yin_yang_grid/130529_yin-yang/130529_yin-yang.html" class=" wrap external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Kageyama / A Mathematica code to draw Yin-Yang grid<i class="icon-external"></i></a></p>


</div>

</div>
